---

<Layout
	title="About West Matcha"
	description="The story behind West Matcha and why we source single-origin, ceremonial-grade matcha directly from Japan."
	pubDate={new Date('July 22 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		West Matcha was founded by J, who grew up in Nagoya, Japan, and now lives in Manitoba,
		Canada. After struggling to find genuinely good matcha in Canada, mostly blends dressed up
		with coloring and sweeteners, J decided to bring the real thing here directly.
	</p>

	<p>
		We source single-origin, ceremonial-grade matcha from tea-growing regions in Japan with deep
		roots in matcha production, including Nishio in Aichi Prefecture. Rather than blending
		leaves from multiple regions for consistency, we focus on single-origin matcha so every
		batch reflects the character of the place it came from.
	</p>

	<p>
		Right now, our focus is introducing Canadians to what real, single-origin matcha actually
		tastes like. Down the road, we plan to expand into flavored matcha latte mixes, think
		strawberry, yuzu, and vanilla, but the matcha at the base of every product will never be
		compromised.
	</p>

	<p>
		Want the full story? Read <a href="/blog/founder-story">how West Matcha began</a>.
	</p>
</Layout>